author":true,"tags":["compsci"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/7fdbnh","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/7fdbnh/apt_graph_colouring"},{"short_id":"fztjyg","created_at":"2026-03-02T06:26:44.000-06:00","title":"Narwhal v0.5.0 – pub/sub messaging server, now powered by io_uring","url":"https://github.com/narwhal-io/narwhal/releases/tag/narwhal-0.5.0","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003ehi again! i'm back with a new release of Narwhal, the lightweight pub/sub server i shared a while ago. the biggest change in v0.5.0 is the migration from tokio to monoio as the primary async runtime, which means the server now runs entirely on io_uring on Linux:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/narwhal-io/narwhal/releases/tag/narwhal-0.5.0\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://github.com/narwhal-io/narwhal/releases/tag/narwhal-0.5.0\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethe project is still alpha, but the core is getting more solid with each release. would love feedback, especially from anyone who has experience tuning io_uring-based servers. i'm sure there's still a lot of room to squeeze more out of it. :)\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"hi again! i'm back with a new release of Narwhal, the lightweight pub/sub server i shared a while ago. the biggest change in v0.5.0 is the migration from tokio to monoio as the primary async runtime, which means the server now runs entirely on io_uring on Linux:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/narwhal-io/narwhal/releases/tag/narwhal-0.5.0\r\n\r\nthe project is still alpha, but the core is getting more solid with each release. would love feedback, especially from anyone who has experience tuning io_uring-based servers. i'm sure there's still a lot of room to squeeze more out of it. :)","submitter_user":"ortuman","user_is_author":true,"tags":["distributed","linux","performance","programming","rust"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fztjyg","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fztjyg/narwhal_v0_